text: Willard Schrader (May 5, 1883 - June 24, 1971) was an American gymnast. He competed in three events at the 1904 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1883 births Category:1971 deaths Category:American male artistic gymnasts Category:Olympic gymnasts of the United States Category:Gymnasts at the 1904 Summer Olympics Category:People from Marion, Indiana
